LORE pyramid-corridor
FLAGS HISTORY MAFDET
Oasis-Pyramid Corridor: eastern desert series of oases and pyramid sites
connected to Mafdet on the coast; treated by scholars as a single system
Great Pyramid: cosmic suppression system for the Black Sun Shard's anti-light;
Solar Court's primary institution; predates current city-building by centuries
Southern Pyramid: Moon Sovereign doctrine (descent-into-darkness as renewal);
Jackal Synod claims funerary authority derived from this tradition
Northern Pyramid: threshold stone inscriptions match Keeper-of-Measure survey
prayer fragments preserved in Kiess Temple of Concord liturgy
Rival excavation camps compete for pyramid site access; no overarching legal
framework; disputes resolved by hired muscle
Quarantine Ledger (Mafdet): handles relic and hazardous pyramid goods;
most politically sensitive Ledger House; recent seizures under sealed review
